Leading Marketing Technology Company, and Lagos-based startup, Plaqad, has, over the past 36 months of operation, signed up over 15,000 influencers, creators, and publishers and has successfully placed over 25,000 pieces of content on social and web platforms across four continents. It has also directly paid out over 200 million naira ($570,000) on hundreds of campaigns to members. According to the company’s Co-founder & CEO, Gbenga Sogbaike, “it has also directly paid out over 200 million naira ($570,000) on hundreds of campaigns to members, effectively helping its programme members monetize their content, platform and influence. “Plaqad uses technology to solve public relations and marketing challenges faced by brands. By democratizing access to the best content creators, influencers and publishers around the world and providing users with the tools to effectively create, track, measure, and optimize their campaigns, we help businesses reach millions of consumers worldwide, irrespective of their size or location,”  he said.